    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Ferny Grove occupies a distinctive position in Brisbane's outer northern corridor. As the terminus of the Ferny Grove train line, it offers direct CBD access that many suburbs with equivalent land and lifestyle credentials cannot match. The suburb's hilly, leafy character and proximity to D'Aguilar National Park and Keperra bushland create a genuine sense of space that appeals strongly to families who have weighed up the trade-off between commute distance and quality of life and decided the Ferny Grove equation works.
    </p>
