    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      I understand what draws buyers to Ferny Grove and what they expect when they arrive to inspect. Presentation standards matter here because the buyers looking in this suburb have often been active across Keperra, Mitchelton and Ferny Hills before extending their search outward. They are comparing carefully and will discount quickly for deferred maintenance that tighter markets absorb.
    </p>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      The topography of Ferny Grove creates genuinely differentiated pockets. Elevated blocks with north-facing aspects and bush outlook consistently attract the strongest buyer interest and command premiums over flat street-level lots. Properties with direct trail access or green outlook onto the surrounding reserve system are a distinct sub-market within the suburb. The Ferny Grove State High School catchment actively drives family-upgrader demand, and the suburb's position as the logical extension of the Keperra and Mitchelton corridor means spill-over buyer demand from those more expensive suburbs is a consistent feature of the local market.
    </p>
    <div style="display:flex; gap:1.5rem; flex-wrap:wrap;">
